<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=805793" target="blank">Magelo Profile</a></div>

<div>Join Date: Jul 2003</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>The usability/usefulness of the Mana Robe is very subjective and personal.  Since a level 1 wizard... going out of mana is the single most dreaded thing i have felt of being a wizard (thought it is essential for balance) ... and since like level 20+ when i learnt about the Manarobe, i have craved for it... up till when i got it when i was 60+... i went into a Norath-wide frenzied celebration... till now.. i still boast my ManaRobe...My point is, Manarobe is like an Epic to me... a status symbol... sumthing like that... As is with a Manastone... i dun use it... but seeing your group's reaction at going from Full health to 10% health in a mere 10 seconds for no rhyme nor reason (to them) is priceless.<br />
<br />
I am still going OOM on ANY fights... be it group grinding, crawling, Time Raids (GOD raids i tend to die before i go oom) ... etc... having that extra ManaRegen Prop of the Mana Robe helps to a certain extent but i would say it is NOT overpowering... after all, it's just/a-whopping 40mana per tick.<br />
<br />
I will never give up my ManaRobe/Manastone ('s effect) for anything... ANYTHING... fine if SOE will never upgrade its effect... BUT DUN YOU DARE TAKE IT AWAY FROM ME!!!<br />
<br />
P.S. as for the comment about changin its effect to a worn FT, etc etc... it's totally crap, period.  Punching the manarobe too much has an opportunity cost (ingame/RL) and isn't that what &quot;balance&quot; is about?<br />
<br />
P.S. #2 For those who votes Option (A) ... either will never have the life to enjoy owning a manarobe... or u got freaking too much Mana and are the uber elitist in which if the case, please pass on your manarobe to mortals like me who actually revere and enjoy having it.  Try giving it to a non-EP wiz and see him go off jumping/celebrating like a series of fire-crackers.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
				Arcanist Seeker of Infinte Mana
